page.title: 08AMPHIBIANS
page.content: {FROGS} Frogs eggs are laid in jelly.The spawn is laid in massive clumps in the moor beside the school,in slow running parts of the river and in Farr Loch in spring. When they hatch out they swim about together.In a few weeks the grow a strong pair of back legs and later a smaller pair of front legs,they can then go on land. {NEWTS} The newt lays its eggs in the same place as frogs and the baby newts eat the tadpoles. {TOADS Toad spawn is differant from frog spawn,frog spawn is in clumps and toad spawn is in a line.
